OL,3,C'It's meant to be such a nice time of
OL,4,Cyear, but for me it was petrifying'
OL,6,FSuzanne Jackson, domestic abuse
OL,7,Fmanager at South Yorkshire Police,
OL,8,Fsaid: "There may still be issues
OL,9,Fregarding child contact. But it isn't
OL,10,Fjust about the victim it's holding
OL,11,Fthat perpetrator to account. If we
OL,12,Fdon't do that, it's that coercive
OL,13,Fcontrol and abusive behaviour that
OL,14,Fcontinues onto the next victim."
OL,16,FSophie found the strength to ask for
OL,17,Fsupport and now uses her own story to
OL,18,Fshow others there is a way to escape.
